  <h1>PomoFomo Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="meta">Last updated: March 2026</p>

  <p>
    PomoFomo is a Chrome browser extension that provides a Pomodoro focus
    timer for children. This policy explains what data the extension handles
    and how.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <p>
    PomoFomo does <strong>not</strong> collect, transmit, store on any server,
    or share any personal information.
  </p>
  <p>The extension stores the following data <strong>locally on your device only</strong>:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Timer settings (focus duration, break duration, character preference, nag mode)</li>
    <li>Timer state (current phase, elapsed time, session count)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    This data never leaves your device. It is not accessible to the extension
    developer or any third party.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h2>Permissions used</h2>
  <p>
    PomoFomo requests the following Chrome permissions solely to operate the
    timer. No permission is used to collect or transmit data.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>alarms</strong> — to advance the timer reliably when the browser is idle</li>
    <li><strong>storage</strong> — to save your settings and timer state on your device</li>
    <li><strong>tabs</strong> — to open, pin, and manage the dedicated timer tab</li>
    <li><strong>notifications</strong> — to alert you when focus or break phases change</li>
  </ul>

  <hr>

  <h2>Third-party services</h2>
  <p>
    PomoFomo makes no network requests and uses no third-party services,
    analytics, advertising, or tracking of any kind.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
  <p>
    PomoFomo is designed for use by children under parental supervision.
    Because the extension collects no data whatsoever, it complies with COPPA
    (the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act) and similar regulations.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    If the extension is ever updated in a way that affects data handling, this
    policy will be updated and the "Last updated" date will change.
  </p>

  <hr>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    If you have questions about this privacy policy, please open an issue at:<br>
    <a href="https://github.com/reticulating-splines/pomofomo">https://github.com/reticulating-splines/pomofomo</a>
  </p>

